title: Caspian Sea Monster
subtitle: Republic of Dagestan, Russia
body: A relic of soviet war efforts, the Korabl Maket was the fastest naval vehicle between 1966 to 1988. It crashed into the Caspian Sea and was beached during efforts to return it home. During operation it cruised at an altatude of around 14m above water and had a top speed of 500 km/h. It was one of the US' prime espionage targets.
